### English Title:
Trump Imposes Additional 145% Tariffs on All Chinese Imports Amid Trade War

### English Text Summary:
President Donald Trump has imposed an additional 145% tariff on all Chinese imports while suspending reciprocal tariffs on other countries, marking a significant shift in trade policy. China has vowed to "fight to the end" against these tariffs, which have escalated the ongoing trade war. The article discusses the impact of these tariffs on U.S. soybean exports, which are heavily affected, and highlights China's efforts to diversify its agricultural imports from other countries, particularly Brazil and Argentina. The U.S. agricultural sector has already suffered significant losses, particularly in soybean production, and farmers are still feeling the repercussions of the trade war.

